cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with communication and dissemination of commands between vehicles in a platoon. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a dynamic programming algorithm to optimize the dissemination latency of the platoon. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with distributed communication and coordination among multiple vehicles. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also possible as the platoon of vehicles can be seen as a multiagent system where each vehicle acts as an agent that needs to coordinate with others. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an algorithm to optimize the dissemination latency, which can be seen as an AI problem.
